headline: Trump Allies See Kevin Hassett as Front-Runner for Vital Economic Job
summary: WASHINGTON—President-elect Donald Trump’s advisers and allies say  Kevin Hassett,  a longtime adviser to Trump, is the front-runner to lead the National Economic Council, according to people familiar with the matter.  As has been the case throughout the transition process, Trump could change his mind and pick someone else for the job, the people cautioned.  During Trump’s first term, Hassett was the chairman of the Council of Economic Advisers, a three-member panel that analyzes economic data on behalf of the president.
